dIdVsuperc-doubleDelta 
Copyright 2008, 2009 Guido De Rosa <guidoderosa@gmail.com>

Fork of dIdVsuperc (hg repository at http://bitbucket.org/gderosa/didvsuperc/).

This fork takes into account the double-gap superconducting feature of 
MgB2 (magnesium diboride) and - presumably - other materials. See, 
for example: F.Giubileo et al, "Strong coupling and double-gap density of 
states in superconducting MgB2", Europhys. Lett., 58 (5), pp. 764â€“770 (2002).

This program is Free Software (see COPYING) and is based on the 
GNU Scientific Library (http://www.gnu.org/software/gsl/).

Developed during a Laboratory course at the University of Naples 
"Federico II", "Dipartimento di Scienze Fisiche".

Thanks to the researchers Roberto Di Capua, Alessandro Gambardella and 
Marco Salluzzo, and to my fellow students Graziano Incalza and Tiziana Spina. 

=======================================================================

You will need (on Unix):
* a C compiler
* CMake               http://www.cmake.org/
* GSL                 http://www.gnu.org/software/gsl/
* Make
* Perl (optional)     http://www.perl.org/
* Gnuplot (optional)  http://www.gnuplot.info/

Simply type:
  cmake .
  make
  ./dIdVsuperc

To build graphical plots (requires Perl and Gnuplot)
  ./util/plot-all.pl

Enjoy!

